In 9-inch pie plate or oven-safe skillet place butter. Heat in 425 degrees F oven for 2 minutes or until melted. Remove from oven. Meanwhile, in blender container combine cereal, eggs, milk, flour and salt. Cover and blend for 15 seconds or until smooth. Pour into hot pie plate. Bake at 425 degrees F for 15 minutes or until golden brown and puffed. Remove from oven. Meanwhile, in small saucepan stir together brown sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon. Gradually stir in apple juice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils and thickens. Stir in apples. Cook, stirring occasionally, until apples soften slightly. Stir in berries, if desired. When pancake comes out of oven, sift icing sugar over top. Cut into wedges and serve immediately with apple topping.